     ‚Ėą  
     ‚Ėą  Co-written by Zak Penn, the screenwriter of movies X2: X-Men 
     ‚Ėą  United and X-Men: The Last Stand, and legendary comic book writer
     ‚Ėą  Chris Claremont, X-Men: The Official Movie Game immerses players 
     ‚Ėą  in an original storyline that provides the back-story for the 
     ‚Ėą  upcoming X-Men: The Last Stand feature film. For the first time
     ‚Ėą  ever, the game enables players to truly command the powers of 
     ‚Ėą  popular characters from the X-Men movie universe by allowing 
     ‚Ėą  players to assume the roles of Wolverine, Nightcrawler, and 
     ‚Ėą  Iceman as they wield and upgrade their signature powers and 
     ‚Ėą  maneuver through unique environments designed to showcase their
     ‚Ėą  Super Hero abilities. Assisted by other X-Men characters, players
     ‚Ėą  will use an advanced control scheme to master and control the 
     ‚Ėą  characters like never before as they unleash Wolverine's combat 
     ‚Ėą  rage, experience Nightcrawler's acrobatics and teleportation 
     ‚Ėą  powers, and glide through the air on Iceman's ice slide.
